What you need to know:

Food security is often considered as having ample food, in terms of quantity. However, food is not just about the quantity, but the quality.hrough organic foods, farmers as well as consumers are protected from non-communicable diseases like cancer, which are highly linked to some agrochemicals.Organic farming when done right is very productive. All farmers need is to maximise space, and apply organic bio-pesticides and bio-fertilisers so that their crops can thrive and produce higher yields.All agriculture requires some-level of labour. Conventional farming simply looks easy because of the use of chemicals, like herbicides instead of weeding.